# neetoUI Usage Rule for Frontend

- Always use neetoUI React components for UI elements (buttons, inputs, typography, modals, panes, tables, etc.) wherever possible.
- Always import and use neetoUI's CSS (`@bigbinary/neetoui/dist/index.css`).
- Always use neetoUI-provided color variables (e.g., `var(--neeto-ui-primary-500)`, `var(--neeto-ui-white)`) for backgrounds, text, and borders. Do not use hardcoded hex, rgb, or custom color values for UI elements.
- Do not use custom or third-party UI libraries for core UI (e.g., do not use Material UI, Ant Design, Bootstrap, etc. for new UI).
- Minimize custom CSS. If custom CSS is needed, use BEM naming and only for layout or non-core UI.
- Do not use Tailwind for theming or core UI.
- Do not use custom font families or font sizes; use neetoUI Typography and its props.
- Use neetoUI spacing, border radius, and shadow variables for layout and effects.
- Exclude translations (i18n) from this rule.

For reference, see the [neetoUI documentation](https://neeto-ui.neeto.com/?path=/docs/welcome--docs).
